# Environment Configuration Example

## Frontend Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the `FrontEnd` directory:

```env
# API Configuration
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
VITE_API_USERS_ENDPOINT=/users/userRegister

# Feature Flags
VITE_ENABLE_PROFILE_PAGE=true
VITE_ENABLE_DELETE_ACCOUNT=true
VITE_ENABLE_PROFILE_UPDATE=true

# Notification Settings
VITE_TOAST_POSITION=top-right
VITE_TOAST_DURATION=3000

# Image Configuration
VITE_DEFAULT_PROFILE_IMAGE=/default-profile-icon.svg
VITE_MAX_IMAGE_SIZE=5242880  # 5MB in bytes

# Analytics (optional)
VITE_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=false
VITE_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID=

# Development Settings
VITE_DEBUG_MODE=false
VITE_LOG_API_CALLS=true
```

## Usage in Code

Update `src/Pages/Profile.jsx` to use environment variables:

```javascript
// Instead of hardcoded URL
const API_BASE = import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL;
const USERS_ENDPOINT = import.meta.env.VITE_API_USERS_ENDPOINT;

// API calls
const profileUrl = `${API_BASE}${USERS_ENDPOINT}/user-Profile`;
const updateUrl = `${API_BASE}${USERS_ENDPOINT}/update-profile`;
const deleteUrl = `${API_BASE}${USERS_ENDPOINT}/delete-account`;
```

## Environment Variables by Stage

### Development (.env.development)
```env
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000
VITE_DEBUG_MODE=true
VITE_LOG_API_CALLS=true
```

### Staging (.env.staging)
```env
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://staging-api.example.com
VITE_DEBUG_MODE=false
VITE_LOG_API_CALLS=true
```

### Production (.env.production)
```env
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com
VITE_DEBUG_MODE=false
VITE_LOG_API_CALLS=false
VITE_ENABLE_ANALYTICS=true
VITE_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID=UA-XXXXXXXXX-X
```

## Vite Configuration

In `vite.config.js`, ensure you're loading environment variables:

```javascript
import { defineConfig } from 'vite'
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
  define: {
    'process.env': JSON.stringify(process.env)
  }
})
```

## Docker Environment Variables (Optional)

If containerizing, pass via Docker:

```dockerfile
ENV VITE_API_BASE_URL=${API_BASE_URL:-http://localhost:3000}
ENV VITE_DEBUG_MODE=${DEBUG_MODE:-false}
```

Run with:
```bash
docker run -e VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com myapp
```

## Building with Different Environments

```bash
# Development
npm run dev

# Build for staging
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://staging-api.example.com npm run build

# Build for production
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com npm run build
```

## Accessing in Components

```javascript
// In any React component
const apiUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL;
const isDebug = import.meta.env.VITE_DEBUG_MODE === 'true';

// Type-safe access with defaults
const getApiUrl = (endpoint) => {
  const baseUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL || 'http://localhost:3000';
  return `${baseUrl}${endpoint}`;
};
```

## Security Notes

⚠️ **Important**: 
- Do NOT store sensitive data in environment variables
- Never commit `.env` files to version control
- Add `.env*` to `.gitignore`
- Use `.env.example` to show required variables
- For sensitive data, use backend environment variables

## GitHub Secrets (For CI/CD)

Add to GitHub Actions secrets:

```yaml
VITE_API_BASE_URL: https://api.example.com
```

Use in workflow:

```yaml
- name: Build
  env:
    VITE_API_BASE_URL: ${{ secrets.API_BASE_URL }}
  run: npm run build
```
